  "body": "Hi,\r\n\r\nwe're experiencing node being behind the tip for cca 200secs, it looks like waves - going up to 200-220secs (last block timestamp vs actual datetime), then it quickly sync up. \r\n\r\nis that a feature or I can improve our config? Using latest 1.4.2 op-node.\r\n\r\n```\r\n      --network=op-mainnet\r\n      --rpc.addr=0.0.0.0\r\n      --rpc.port=<port>\r\n      --p2p.disable\r\n      --l1=<l1 url>\r\n      --l2=<l2 url>\r\n      --l2.jwt-secret=/shared/jwt.txt\r\n      --l1.max-concurrency 20\r\n      --l1.rpc-max-batch-size 60\r\n      --l1.http-poll-interval 1s\r\n      --l1.epoch-poll-interval 60s\r\n      --p2p.peers.hi 50\r\n```\r\n\r\ntried to play with `max-concurrency` and the rest, no effect.\r\n\r\nnode: 128G RAM, NVME, 32 cores AMD EPYC 7371\r\n\r\nThanks\r\ntom",
